      <title>Re: Class issues lists – Updated Version (Ranger)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=16310#M16310</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff00ff&gt;Ranger - List Update scheduled for&amp;nbsp;03/04/05&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;1.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Increase DPS &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;- (Add triple attack,&amp;nbsp;new melee tables,&amp;nbsp;disciplines, improved DDs, etc) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;DPS for all classes to be evaluated with the class Re-Envision process&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Ranger has continually been thought of as a DPS class in the arena of rogues and monks, though through the melee increases and the toggling between archery and melee focii for rangers, the class has lost it's footing in the DPS hierarchy and needs to be solidly reinstated as a&amp;nbsp;damage dealing&amp;nbsp;class.&amp;nbsp; Many things can be done to remedy this, addition of Triple attack, Improved scaling itemization, decreasing casting time on nukes (see issue 9), moving rangers to monk tables, etc.&amp;nbsp; Rangers are tired of being considered "half a rogue" when looking at dps.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;2.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Harmony of Nature line of spells&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;(allow Harmony to be used indoors with restrictions)&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Removed the reference to adding an upgrade since this is complete.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;3.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Increase avoidance&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (increase the cap for riposte, cap for dodge, soft AC cap, and decrease riposte damage when dual wielding) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;When looking at the&amp;nbsp;hierarchy of tanking ability, the ranger has slowly lost it's footing here as well.&amp;nbsp; With the onset of incredibly high damage mobs, riposte damage has nearly crippled the ranger for tanking, coupled with the poor avoidance caps versus other chain and leather classes and a poor soft AC cap, rangers have lost much of their ability to tank.&amp;nbsp; Rangers do have a taunt button, but have no reason to use it right now at all when compared to other classes.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;4.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Archery (&lt;/STRONG&gt;Keep inline with melee gains, upgrade less desireable aspects such as no autoattack* and no minimum damage, better supplemental archery upgrades ie: quivers, arrows)&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;General improvements to archery are being discussed as part of the re-envision process.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;While it's been said by developers that rangers' focus should be melee, the fact remains that many, if not the majority of, rangers utilize the their bow as their primary form of damage.&amp;nbsp; This is an important aspect of rangerdom and the most important to many rangers.&amp;nbsp; It should not be ignored as it has been since the plane of time as far as high end progression and at levels 1-55.&amp;nbsp; While remaining overpowered at a very small stage in a ranger's career, it has become very underpowered in all other stages.&amp;nbsp; And of course, make archery mods actually work&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;5.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improved heals&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (increase the hit points healed, reduce re-cast timer, decrease the gap between Druid and Ranger heals) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;With the onset of the new Omens heal for rangers, it seems as if healing ability could be headed in the correct direction, though when compared to the efficiency of our parent class for healing versus other hybrids and their parents, we are well behind the curve.&amp;nbsp; It's understood that rangers shouldn't be primary healers, but with the current hit point levels and damage outputs of mobs, ranger's healing ability has melted into spamming intelligence casters during downtime.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;6.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improved Disciplines&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (Add Melee Disciplines, reduce current discipline timers) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Being recently told that&amp;nbsp;rangers are intended to be a melee class rather than a ranged damage class, it begs the question, why don't rangers have an offensive melee discipline?&amp;nbsp; With this, the current level increase has not cut down the reuse timer for existing disciplines and their already enormous reuse times.&amp;nbsp; Even more accepted, would be an AA to reduce the 67 minute wait on ranger (and all hybrid) diciplines.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;7.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Auspice of the Hunter /&amp;nbsp;Increase raid&amp;nbsp;desirability&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;(specifically, improve Auspice of the Hunter, and consider other desireability options)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Rashere is currently evaluating Auspice of the Hunter.&amp;nbsp; He feels it may need a boost however it will not be a huge boost since this can affect an entire raid.&amp;nbsp; Suggestions and feedback can be added to &lt;A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;amp;message.id=12125" target=_blank&gt;&lt;FONT color=#cccccc&gt;this thread.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;With the addition of "Auspice of the Hunter" it seems at first glance that we have been answered, but through parses it shows just how little this adds to a raid or group.&amp;nbsp; In raids, it's been parsed out to adding around 3-4k damage or one non crit wizard nuke.&amp;nbsp; In single groups, it's actually been found to decrease dps due to the minor bonus, and loss of melee damage while casting.&amp;nbsp; Along with that, with it's very diminished increase, it adds nothing to group desirabilty, and very very little to raid desirability.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;8.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Buff Problems&lt;/STRONG&gt; - Improve Spirit of Hunter line and&amp;nbsp;Ward of the Hunter&amp;nbsp;lines of spells (Ward of the Hunter buff inclusion and stacking,&amp;nbsp;Spirit of the Hunter&amp;nbsp;line desireability, lack of any caster buffs, diminishing&amp;nbsp;returns on&amp;nbsp;attack at high levels) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being&amp;nbsp;discussed, this will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;No, rangers have never been great buffers, and never wanted to be.&amp;nbsp; But, rangers deserve some more consideration on their bufflines, specifically: Protection of the Wild line of spells including more self buffs, Spirit of Tunare line desirablity compared to other hybrids, Spirit of the Predator lines desirability with diminishing high level attack totals, lack of any caster desireable buff, basic stacking issues with self buffs and targetable buffs.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Ranger Notes -&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Combination buff PotW should combine more ranger buffs&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Spirit of the Hunter's desiriability increased vs Paladin and Beastlord line buffs&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Lack of any Caster desireable buff&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Diminishing returns on high level attack which is involved in most ranger buffs&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Upgrade to our "druid replacement" buff to be more inline with other hybrids&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;9.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Ranger Direct Damage Spells&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;(Reduce casting and recast time, decrease resist rates, increase damage)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being&amp;nbsp;discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Ranger direct damage at this point in the game can often net negative DPS due to resist rates, partial resists, and casting times.&amp;nbsp; A two second casting time does not effect a beastlord or shadowknight as much as it does a ranger due to our melee DPS.&amp;nbsp; This coupled with recast timers mandating our mana usage rather than allowing the ranger to apply their mana has reduced our direct damage spell usefulness dramatically over time.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;10.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;STRONG&gt;Snare and Root issues&lt;/STRONG&gt; (Improve snare and root to increase it's usefulness in current content) &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;With the slow decline of ranger damage and utility, rangers have found a nitche for themselves in assisting with crowd control.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Through the agro production of snare and other spells, rangers have been able to draw mobs out of groups, and using the same skills, taunt mobs off of players that they shouldn't be on.&amp;nbsp; With snare agro stagnating compared to other agro abilities (intentional and unintentional) this ability has been nearly lost with the stagnation of our antiquated level 51 snare and level 9 agro spells.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Add in the completely ridiculous resist rate of snare on non debuffed mobs, and it's usefulness has slid even more.&amp;nbsp; The same holds true for root, with quick breaks and mob immunity, the days of rangers helping with CC have all but completely died out.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sat, 05 Mar 2005 02:13:22 GMT</pubDate>
      <author>Ashlanne</author>
      <guid>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=16310#M16310</guid>
      <dc:creator>Ashlanne</dc:creator>
      <dc:date>2005-03-05T02:13:22Z</dc:date>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Re: Class issues lists – Updated Version (Ranger)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;message.id=16005#M16005</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:&gt;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: mso-margin-top-alt: 0pt; 0in auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff00ff&gt;Ranger - List Update scheduled for&amp;nbsp;02/07/05&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;SPAN Verdana? #cccccc; FONT-FAMILY: **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;1.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Increase DPS &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;- (Add triple attack,&amp;nbsp;new melee tables,&amp;nbsp;disciplines, improved DDs, etc) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;DPS for all classes to be evaluated with the class Re-Envision process&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Ranger has continually been thought of as a DPS class in the arena of rogues and monks, though through the melee increases and the toggling between archery and melee focii for rangers, the class has lost it's footing in the DPS hierarchy and needs to be solidly reinstated as a&amp;nbsp;damage dealing&amp;nbsp;class.&amp;nbsp; Many things can be done to remedy this, addition of Triple attack, Improved scaling itemization, decreasing casting time on nukes (see issue 9), moving rangers to monk tables, etc.&amp;nbsp; Rangers are tired of being considered "half a rogue" when looking at dps.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;2.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Harmony of Nature line of spells&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;(allow Harmony to be used indoors with restrictions)&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Removed the reference to adding an upgrade since this is complete.&amp;nbsp; Would it be possible to get some more definition to this item?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;3.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Increase avoidance&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (increase the cap for riposte, cap for dodge, soft AC cap, and decrease riposte damage when dual wielding) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;When looking at the&amp;nbsp;hierarchy of tanking ability, the ranger has slowly lost it's footing here as well.&amp;nbsp; With the onset of incredibly high damage mobs, riposte damage has nearly crippled the ranger for tanking, coupled with the poor avoidance caps versus other chain and leather classes and a poor soft AC cap, rangers have lost much of their ability to tank.&amp;nbsp; Rangers do have a taunt button, but have no reason to use it right now at all when compared to other classes.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;4.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Archery (&lt;/STRONG&gt;Keep inline with melee gains, upgrade less desireable aspects such as no autoattack* and no minimum damage, better supplemental archery upgrades ie: quivers, arrows)&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;General improvements to archery are being discussed.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;While it's been said by developers that rangers' focus should be melee, the fact remains that many, if not the majority of, rangers utilize the their bow as their primary form of damage.&amp;nbsp; This is an important aspect of rangerdom and the most important to many rangers.&amp;nbsp; It should not be ignored as it has been since the plane of time as far as high end progression and at levels 1-55.&amp;nbsp; While remaining overpowered at a very small stage in a ranger's career, it has become very underpowered in all other stages.&amp;nbsp; And of course, make archery mods actually work&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;5.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improved heals&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (increase the hit points healed, reduce re-cast timer, decrease the gap between Druid and Ranger heals) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;With the onset of the new Omens heal for rangers, it seems as if healing ability could be headed in the correct direction, though when compared to the efficiency of our parent class for healing versus other hybrids and their parents, we are well behind the curve.&amp;nbsp; It's understood that rangers shouldn't be primary healers, but with the current hit point levels and damage outputs of mobs, ranger's healing ability has melted into spamming intelligence casters during downtime.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;6.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improved Disciplines&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (Add Melee Disciplines, reduce current discipline timers) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Being recently told that&amp;nbsp;rangers are intended to be a melee class rather than a ranged damage class, it begs the question, why don't rangers have an offensive melee discipline?&amp;nbsp; With this, the current level increase has not cut down the reuse timer for existing disciplines and their already enormous reuse times.&amp;nbsp; Even more accepted, would be an AA to reduce the 67 minute wait on ranger (and all hybrid) diciplines.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;7.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Auspice of the Hunter /&amp;nbsp;Increase raid&amp;nbsp;desirability&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;(specifically, improve Auspice of the Hunter, and consider other desireability options)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Rashere is currently evaluating Auspice of the Hunter.&amp;nbsp; He feels it may need a boost however it will not be a huge boost since this can affect an entire raid.&amp;nbsp; Suggestions and feedback can be added to &lt;A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=rangerbalance&amp;amp;message.id=12125" target=_blank&gt;&lt;FONT color=#f0a911&gt;this thread.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;With the addition of "Auspice of the Hunter" it seems at first glance that we have been answered, but through parses it shows just how little this adds to a raid or group.&amp;nbsp; In raids, it's been parsed out to adding around 3-4k damage or one non crit wizard nuke.&amp;nbsp; In single groups, it's actually been found to decrease dps due to the minor bonus, and loss of melee damage while casting.&amp;nbsp; Along with that, with it's very diminished increase, it adds nothing to group desirabilty, and very very little to raid desirability.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;8.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Buff Problems&lt;/STRONG&gt; - Improve Spirit of Hunter line and&amp;nbsp;Ward of the Hunter&amp;nbsp;lines of spells (Ward of the Hunter buff inclusion and stacking,&amp;nbsp;Spirit of the Hunter&amp;nbsp;line desireability, lack of any caster buffs, diminishing&amp;nbsp;returns on&amp;nbsp;attack at high levels) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being&amp;nbsp;discussed, this will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;No, rangers have never been great buffers, and never wanted to be.&amp;nbsp; But, rangers deserve some more consideration on their bufflines, specifically: Protection of the Wild line of spells including more self buffs, Spirit of Tunare line desirablity compared to other hybrids, Spirit of the Predator lines desirability with diminishing high level attack totals, lack of any caster desireable buff, basic stacking issues with self buffs and targetable buffs.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Ranger Notes -&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Combination buff PotW should combine more ranger buffs&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Spirit of the Hunter's desiriability increased vs Paladin and Beastlord line buffs&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Lack of any Caster desireable buff&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Diminishing returns on high level attack which is involved in most ranger buffs&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Upgrade to our "druid replacement" buff to be more inline with other hybrids&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;9.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Ranger Direct Damage Spells&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;(Reduce casting and recast time, decrease resist rates, increase damage)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being&amp;nbsp;discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Ranger direct damage at this point in the game can often net negative DPS due to resist rates, partial resists, and casting times.&amp;nbsp; A two second casting time does not effect a beastlord or shadowknight as much as it does a ranger due to our melee DPS.&amp;nbsp; This coupled with recast timers mandating our mana usage rather than allowing the ranger to apply their mana has reduced our direct damage spell usefulness dramatically over time.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;10.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;STRONG&gt;Snare and Root issues&lt;/STRONG&gt; (Improve snare and root to increase it's usefulness in current content) &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;With the slow decline of ranger damage and utility, rangers have found a nitche for themselves in assisting with crowd control.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Through the agro production of snare and other spells, rangers have been able to draw mobs out of groups, and using the same skills, taunt mobs off of players that they shouldn't be on.&amp;nbsp; With snare agro stagnating compared to other agro abilities (intentional and unintentional) this ability has been nearly lost with the stagnation of our antiquated level 51 snare and level 9 agro spells.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Add in the completely ridiculous resist rate of snare on non debuffed mobs, and it's usefulness has slid even more.&amp;nbsp; The same holds true for root, with quick breaks and mob immunity, the days of rangers helping with CC have all but completely died out.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
