&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff00ff&gt;Ranger - List Update scheduled for&amp;nbsp;10/8/04&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in auto? justify; TEXT-ALIGN: mso-margin-top-alt: mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; 0pt; **Oompa-Loompa**?MARGIN:&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **SMURF**?COLOR: #cccccc;&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff00ff&gt;Please note that there isn't any new development feedback on this list.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? #cccccc; **Oompa-Loompa**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: COLOR: mso-fareast-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; #cccccc;&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: COLOR: mso-fareast-font-family: **SMURF**?FONT-SIZE: 9pt; #cccccc;&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;1.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt; &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Increase DPS &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;- &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;DPS for all classes to be re-evaluated in the future&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Ranger has continually been thought of as a DPS class in the arena of rouges and monks, though through the melee increases and the toggling between archery and melee focii for rangers, the class has lost it's footing in the DPS hierarchy and needs to be solidly reinstated as a&amp;nbsp;damage dealing&amp;nbsp;class.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;2.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Increase avoidance&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (increase the cap for riposte and dodge and allow riposte damage when dual wielding) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;When looking at the&amp;nbsp;hierarchy of tanking ability, the ranger has slowly lost it's footing here as well.&amp;nbsp; With the onset of incredibly high damage mobs, riposte damage has nearly crippled the ranger for tanking, coupled with the poor avoidance caps versus other chain and leather classes, rangers have lost much of their ability to tank.&amp;nbsp; Rangers do have a taunt button, but have no reason to use it right now at all when compared to other classes.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;3.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Archery&lt;/STRONG&gt; (Keep inline with melee gains, upgrade less desireable aspects such as no autoattack and no minimum damage, better supplimental archery upgrades ie: quivers, arrows)&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;This item was revised with the update on 9/24/04, there isn't any feedback on this item yet.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#818181&gt;&lt;SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:&gt;&lt;xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" &gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;While it's been said by developers that rangers' focus should be melee, the fact remains that many, if not the majority of, rangers utilize the their bow as their primary form of damage.&amp;nbsp; This is an important aspect of rangerdom and the most important to many rangers.&amp;nbsp; It should not be ignored as it has been since the plane of time as far as high end progression and at levels 1-55.&amp;nbsp; While remaining overpowered at a very small stage in a ranger's career, it has become very underpowered in all other stages.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;4.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improved heals&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (increase the hit points healed, reduce re-cast timer, decrease the gap between Druid and Ranger heals) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;With the onset of the new Omens heal for rangers, it seems as if healing ability could be headed in the correct direction, though when compared to the efficiency of our parent class for healing versus other hybrids and their parents, we are well behind the curve.&amp;nbsp; It's understood that rangers shouldn't be primary healers, but with the current hit point levels and damage outputs of mobs, ranger's healing ability has melted into spamming intelligence casters during downtime.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;5.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improved Disciplines&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; (Reduce reuse timers, Add Melee Disciplines) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Being recently told that we are intended to be a melee class rather than a ranged damage class, it begs the question, why don't rangers have an offensive melee discipline?&amp;nbsp; With this, the current level increase has not cut down the reuse timer for existing disciplines and their already enormous reuse times.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;6.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Track&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being&amp;nbsp;discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;At&amp;nbsp;the onset of GoD, rangers were excited to hear&amp;nbsp;that devs had planned to better ranger tracking and different ideas were being discussed.&amp;nbsp; Somehow that was scrapped, and&amp;nbsp;rangers recieved no tracking increase while other classes did (skill only).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;With the&amp;nbsp;"magic path"&amp;nbsp;of&amp;nbsp;the find PC group ability, it would seem reasonable that rangers should get some sort of "bells and&amp;nbsp;whistles" upgrade to tracking, rather than just blanket skill icnreases.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;7.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Class unique skills that make Rangers desirable for groups and raids&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;This isn't as easy as other requests to explain, so I'll simply give examples.&amp;nbsp; Paladins have LoH, Mages have Coth, Rogues have SoS, Warriors are the best tanks, Clerics are the best healers, and rangers don't seem to have any raid defining ability like any other class.&amp;nbsp; As you can see, this isn't a simple request, but more a plea for "something" that can add to ranger desireability.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Suggestions –&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;•&amp;nbsp;Some sort of unique ability that rangers can offer to a raid or group&lt;BR&gt;•&amp;nbsp;Special spell or ability that can be MGB'd&lt;BR&gt;•&amp;nbsp;General group desirability for the ranger class&lt;BR&gt;•&amp;nbsp;General raid desirability for the ranger class&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;8&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve the Harmony line of spells&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;(add an upgrade to harmony for Rangers in Omens, allow Harmony to be used indoors with restrictions) &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being&amp;nbsp;discussed&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Rangers have always been "woodsman", superior in the outdoors.&amp;nbsp; Maybe the most defining characteristic of that was our harmony spell.&amp;nbsp; With Omens, rangers have been completely stripped of that ability.&amp;nbsp; This is a basic game function of rangers that has been completely forgotten, and needs to be reimplimented, hopefully to the point that it can add to ranger pulling abilities indoors possibly as well.&amp;nbsp; If not, even more stability in our outdoor pulling.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;9.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Buffs &lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being&amp;nbsp;discussed&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;No, rangers have never been great buffers, and never wanted to be.&amp;nbsp; But, rangers deserve some more consideration on their bufflines, specifically: Protection of the Wild line of spells including more self buffs, Spirit of Tunare line desireablity compared to other hybrids, Spirit of the Predator lines desireability with diminishing high level attack totals, lack of any caster desireable buff, basic stacking issues with self buffs and targetable buffs.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Ranger Notes -&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;• Combination of buffs in Protection of the Wild should add more ranger self buffs&lt;BR&gt;• Desirability of Strength of Tunare in regards to Brells and Spiritual Vigor&lt;BR&gt;• Stacking issues with PotW and other buffs (Brells, Damage shields, etc)&lt;BR&gt;• Issue of so many other ranger self buffs (Nature's Percision, Cry of Thunder, Eagle Eye, Wolf form etc)&lt;BR&gt;• Lack of any caster desirable buff&lt;BR&gt;• Issue of so many other ranger self buffs (Nature's Percision, Cry of Thunder, Eagle Eye, Wolf form etc)&lt;BR&gt;• Force of Nature stacking issues and lack of upgrades&lt;BR&gt;• Diminishing returns on high level attack creating less need for Spirit of the Predator line spells&lt;BR&gt;• Call of Rathe stacking issues with click effect items (Fiery Might, Vengeful Guard, Frostweaver's blessing, etc)&lt;BR&gt;• Feral Form has a 40% speed increase which actually slows rangers with run 5&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;10&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;.&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Improve Ranger Direct Damage Spells&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;(Reduce casting and recast time, decrease resist rates, increase damage)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being&amp;nbsp;discussed&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Ranger direct damage at this point in the game can often net negative DPS due to resist rates, partial resists, and casting times.&amp;nbsp; A two second casting time does not effect a beastlord or shadowknight as much as it does a ranger due to our melee DPS.&amp;nbsp; This coupled with recast timers mandating our mana usage rather than allowing the ranger to apply their mana has reduced our direct damage spell usefulness dramatically.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
